PREPARATIONS are in top gear for the release of the maiden album of Jazz musician, Edwin Utere, who is more known as Ed Izycs. The album titled ‘Gold’ has 13 tracks and two bonus tracks. And speaking to The Nation newspaper, Ed Izycs said the album which will be launched on April 12 in Lagos represents how he sees his music. This is coming about a month after the artiste clocked 29. The self-taught jazz musician was discovered by Cadilly Entertainment in 2014 after he published the video of one of his songs, ‘Celebration’ on Youtube. And since his discovery, Ed Izycs has released other songs, including an EP. He has also performed on stages across Nigeria, Uganda and South Africa.